(secondQuint)Effects of Estrogen and Hot Flashes on Mood in Postmenopausal Women.

 SPECIFIC AIMS (Research Objectives) To define the relative effects of hot flashes and changes in estradiol on mood in postmenopausal women: Hypotheses: 1.

 Estrogen treatment has a similar therapeutic effect on mood in women with and without frequent hot flashes 2.

 Estradiol levels correlate with improvement in mood.

 Effects of Estrogen and Hot Flashes on Mood in Postmenopausal Women@highlight

This protocol is a controlled study of estradiol therapy in early postmenopausal women with and without frequent hot flashes that will be used to determine whether hot flashes are an important intermediary in the generation of menopause-associated depression.

